    </assertion><omtext class="name">
      <CMP> a(i)=the number of occurrences of 7s in the palindromic compositions of n=2*i-1 = the number of occurrences of 8s in the palindromic compositions of n=2*i.</CMP>
    </omtext><omtext class="comment">
      <CMP> This sequence is part of a family of sequences, namely R(n,k), the number of ks in palindromic compositions of n. See also A057711, A001792, A078836, A079861, A079862. General formula: R(n,k)=2^(floor(n/2) - k) * (2 + floor(n/2) - k) if n and k have different parity and R(n,k)=2^(floor(n/2) - k) * (2 + floor(n/2) - k + 2^(floor((k+1)/2 - 1)) otherwise, for n &gt;= 2k.</CMP>
    </omtext><omtext class="link">
